Package com.syncura360.model

package com.syncura360.model
Contains the core domain model classes (entities, value objects) representing application data structures.
  • Related Packages
    Package
    Description
    com.syncura360
    Provides the core classes for the Syncura360 application.
    com.syncura360.model.enums
    Provides enumeration types used throughout the application, often defining states or types within the domain model.
    com.syncura360.controller
    Contains REST API controllers responsible for handling HTTP requests and responses.
    com.syncura360.dto
    Defines Data Transfer Objects (DTOs) used for carrying data between layers or across API boundaries.
    com.syncura360.repository
    Defines repository interfaces and implementations for data access and persistence operations.

    Includes classes related to application security, such as configuration, authentication, and authorization.
    com.syncura360.service
    Implements the core business logic and orchestration layer, coordinating actions between controllers and repositories.
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    Bed
    Entity representing a bed in a hospital, associated with a specific room and status.
    Drug
    Entity representing a drug in the system, including its details like name, category, description, strength, price, and quantity.
    DrugAdministered
    Entity representing a drug administered to a patient, including the drug, visit, and the staff who administered it.
    DrugAdministeredId
    Embeddable composite ID for identifying a drug administered to a patient, including hospital ID, patient ID, visit admission date, and administered time.
    DrugId
    Embeddable composite ID for identifying a drug, including hospital ID and drug NDC (National Drug Code).
    Equipment
    Entity representing an equipment item in a hospital room, including its ID, name, and maintenance status.
    EquipmentId
    Embeddable composite ID for identifying equipment in a hospital, including hospital ID, room name, and equipment serial number.
    Hospital
    Entity representing a hospital, including its details such as name, address, contact information, trauma level, and facilities.
    PatientInfo
    Entity representing a patient's personal and medical information, including demographics, contact details, and medical history.
    PatientLogin
    Entity representing a patient's login credentials, including username, password hash, and associated email.
    Room
    Entity representing a room in a hospital, including its unique identifier, associated hospital, and department.
    RoomAssignment
    Entity representing a room assignment for a patient during a visit, including its unique identifier, associated room, and removal status.
    RoomAssignmentId
    Composite primary key class for identifying a room assignment for a patient during a visit, based on hospital, patient, visit admission time, and assignment time.
    RoomId
    Composite primary key class for identifying a room in a hospital, based on hospital ID and room name.
    Schedule
    Represents a schedule entity with details like staff, department, and end date-time.
    ScheduleId
    Represents the composite primary key for the Schedule entity.
    Service
    Represents a service offered by a hospital, with details like category, description, and cost.
    ServiceId
    Represents a service offered by a hospital, with details like category, description, and cost.
    ServiceProvided
    Represents a service provided to a patient during a visit, including details like the staff who performed it and the service itself.
    ServiceProvidedId
    Represents the composite primary key for the ServiceProvided entity, consisting of hospital ID, patient ID, and visit admission date-time.
    Staff
    Represents a staff member working at a hospital, including personal and professional details.
    Visit
    Represents a visit to a hospital, including details such as the patient, hospital, and reason for visit.
    VisitId
    Represents the composite primary key for the Visit entity, consisting of hospital ID, patient ID, and admission date-time.
